the GST is the first federal tax on reading in Canada ' s history . 
provinces have never taxed books . 
literacy learners who mostly buy their own materials must pay tax . 
parents who buy their children books must pay tax . 
we recognize there are GST credits and other educational credits for students , but these do not make up for the fact that we tax textbooks . 
